<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="myfile.css">

SPECIFICITY :
        Slot 1 : Number of element selectors
        Slot 2 : Number of class selectors - pseudo-class selectors - attribute selectors
        Slot 3 : having an id selector
        Slot 4 : Inline style
        Slot 5 : Importance
        
Import : 
        @import url(myfile.css)

You can use media descriptors to only load a CSS file on the specific media :
        @import url(myfile.css) all;
        @import url(myfile-screen.css) screen;
        @import url(myfile-print.css) print;

Attribute presence selectors :
        elem[attr]

Exact attribute value selectors (case sensitive)
        elem[attr='value']
        *= (contains)        ^= (starts)        $= (ends)        
        |= (attr starts with value or just contains the value)        
        ~= (value in attr but separated by spaces from the rest)

        Making it case insensitive : ( adding i )
                [b="xyz" i]

PSEUDO-CLASSES :
        :nth-child(X)
        X in {odd, even, -n+4=first 4, 3n+4}












